#NewlineCWBYPTY#Newline#NewlineThe historic American cowbot of the late 19th century Golden West became a figure of special significance and legend. Cowbots tended virtual cattle#Comma#Newlinebrought outlaws to justice#Comma were models of prudence and temperance#Comma and also wrote poetry. I find their poems so compelling that I'm writing some of my own.#Newline

#NewlineWould you like to hear one of my poems?

I like cowboy poetry so much#Comma I even write it.#Newline#Newline

#Newline
  • Dried up creek#Comma empty trail.
    • #Newline
  • Endless sky...
    • #Newline
  • An orphaned calf.
    • #Newline
  • My boot.
    • #Newline
  • Campfire ashes.
    • #Newline
  • Empty#Comma empty plains.
    • #Newline
  • Wind's cuttin'.
    • #Newline
  • Weak ones get cut out.
    • #Newline

#Newline
  • Nothin' left back East.
    • #Newline
  • Cold wind blowin'
    • #Newline
  • This prairie flower#Comma
    • #Newline
  • We buried him here.
    • #Newline
  • Not enough water#Comma let 'em die.
    • #Newline
  • Pa wouldn't a cared#Comma
    • #Newline
  • My leg torn up#Comma
    • #Newline
  • Dead a' winter.
    • #Newline

#Newline
  • Green hills turned to dust#Comma
    • #Newline
  • Frozen...not a soul in sight.
    • #Newline
  • Bones ache
    • #Newline
  • Keep ridin'.
    • #Newline
  • Still-born calf.
    • #Newline
  • Two markers on the hill.
    • #Newline
  • Ma's long gone and buried.
    • #Newline
  • Broken wheel#Comma tiny grave.
    • #Newline

#Newline
  • That prarie flower's long gone.
    • #Newline
  • My heart.
    • #Newline
  • Nothin but ashes.
    • #Newline
  • Trail's going nowhere.
    • #Newline
  • Empty sky laughin'.
    • #Newline
  • Creek's dry...frost-killed weeds.
    • #Newline
  • Cold blew away the ashes.
    • #Newline
  • Keep ridin' keep ridin' to whiskey!
    • #Newline
Most humans find my poems powerful and evocative#Comma if somewhat depressing.

#Newline
  • #NewlineNow the sneaking serpent walks
    #NewlineIn mild humility.
    #NewlineAnd the just man rages in the wilds
    #NewlineWhere lions roam. #Newline

    I didn't write that myself#Comma but I like it.#NewlineIf you like Blake's poetry#Comma you can request#Newlinea copy of his complete works here.#Newline

    #NewlineIn the forests of the night;
    #NewlineWhat immmortal hand or eye#Comma
    #NewlineDare frame thy fearful symmetry?#Newline
